{
  "stem": "11274.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I know she, she was 16 years older than I, you know, 16 years before me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Zosia was-- two years later, Zosia was born.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So World War I came.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were two girls-- World War I-- Gertrude and Zosia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And during World War I, two boys were born.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I think it's the influenza, or whatever it was at this time there and, and-- it was all over the world, actually, influenza-- and the two boys died before there was a chance to get them some medication.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then-- then 1920, after the war, two years, and I was born.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And two years later, 1922, my sister Danka was born.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents were Jewish Orthodox, very religious.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother was born in Czechoslovakia, married very young, I think 17 or 18.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father was born in Tylicz and he was a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know how to say it-- to yeshiva was going in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was an arranged marriage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were very happy, happy couple.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was a loving, lovely, wonderful family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all the 25 families, Jewish, lived with the Gentiles, the Ruthenians, and the Polish people in peace and harmony.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We didn't know ecumenical, the word ecumenical, what it meant, but we lived by it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we didn't-- I didn't know, really, much about anti-Semitism or, or any harsh, harsh things about, about it during the life when I was growing up.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then the, the, the, the Greek Orthodox had their own school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Polish school was for the Polish children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jewish children attended the Polish public schools, seven years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what else would you like?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't have a rabbi in the town, but we had a shochet, which is a ritual slaughterer.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
